    • Uses of LV in org.jungrapht.visualization.layout.algorithms.sugiyama

      Classes in org.jungrapht.visualization.layout.algorithms.sugiyama that implement LV 
      Modifier and Type Class Description
      class  LVI<V>
      Implementation of a vertex type for a layered layout algorithm.
      Instances of LVI<V> replace instances of V during layout The LVI<V> holds metadata information about the position of the vertex in the layered graph.
      class  SyntheticLV<V>
      a vertex that is not in the original graph, but is synthesized in order to position bends in the articulated edges of the SugiyamaLayoutAlgorithm
